  "prompt": "How do I prepare GK for the AIIMS?",
  "response": "To prepare General Knowledge (GK) for AIIMS, follow these strategies:\n\n1. Study Resources:\n- NCERT textbooks\n- Current affairs magazines\n- Newspapers (The Hindu, Indian Express)\n- Online GK portals\n- Previous year question papers\n\n2. Focus Areas:\n- National and International events\n- Scientific discoveries\n- Sports achievements\n- Awards and honors\n- Government schemes\n- Indian history and culture\n- Basic science and technology\n- Environmental issues\n\n3. Preparation Techniques:\n- Read newspapers daily\n- Make concise notes\n- Follow current affairs regularly\n- Watch news channels\n- Use monthly GK magazines\n- Practice mock tests\n- Join online GK forums\n\n4. Recommended Magazines:\n- Pratiyogita Darpan\n- Competition Success Review\n- Yojana\n- Frontline\n\n5. Online Resources:\n- Websites like Jagran Josh\n- BYJU'S current affairs\n- GK Today website\n- YouTube current affairs channels\n\n6. Time Management:\n- Dedicate 1-2 hours daily\n- Revise notes regularly\n- Create flashcards\n- Take weekly quizzes\n\n7. Additional Tips:\n- Focus on understanding, not memorizing\n- Connect current events with static GK\n- Stay updated with recent developments\n\nConsistent and systematic preparation is key to success.",
